10️⃣ Permanent kubeconfig Fix (vagrant user)

Already applied via inline provisioner in Vagrantfile:

mkdir -p /home/vagrant/.kube
cp -i /etc/kubernetes/admin.conf /home/vagrant/.kube/config
chown vagrant:vagrant /home/vagrant/.kube/config

Runs automatically every boot (run: "always").

No need to redo manually.

11️⃣ Lab Quick Commands Summary
Action	Command
Start all VMs	vagrant up
Stop all VMs	vagrant halt
Reload + provision master	vagrant reload --provision k8s-master
Destroy all VMs	vagrant destroy -f
SSH into a VM	vagrant ssh <vm-name>
Check status	vagrant status
Run provisioners	vagrant provision or vagrant provision <vm>

This cheat-sheet ensures you can start, stop, destroy, reprovision, and check everything in your lab quickly — plus kubectl, Jenkins, and SonarQube tips.